1
00:00:35,087 --> 00:00:37,948
BILBAO, SPAIN

2
00:00:45,288 --> 00:00:51,088
So good of you to come, Mr. Bond,
particularly on such short notice.

3
00:00:51,248 --> 00:00:54,927
If you can't trust a Swiss banker,
what's the world come to?

4
00:00:55,168 --> 00:00:58,009
"Bon." Now that we're all comfortable,

5
00:00:58,249 --> 00:01:01,170
why don't you sit down?

6
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:05,409
It was not easy,
but I have retrieved the money.

7
00:01:05,649 --> 00:01:09,569
No doubt Sir Robert
will be pleased to see it again.

8
00:01:09,809 --> 00:01:13,410
At the current rate of exchange,
minus the fees and certain

9
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:16,369
unforeseeable expenses.
"Voilá." Your receipt.

10
00:01:16,609 --> 00:01:20,171
Would you like to check my figures?

11
00:01:20,291 --> 00:01:24,010
Oh, I'm sure they're perfectly rounded.

12
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:27,891
- It's all there.
- I didn't come for the money.

13
00:01:28,131 --> 00:01:34,412
The report Sir Robert bought was stolen
from an MI6 agent who was killed for it.

14
00:01:35,812 --> 00:01:37,611
I want to know who killed him.

15
00:01:37,851 --> 00:01:40,452
- Terrible tragedy.
- I just want a name.

16
00:01:40,692 --> 00:01:46,612
I am merely the middleman. I'm just
returning the money to its rightful owner.

17
00:01:46,852 --> 00:01:51,772
And we know how difficult that can be
for a Swiss banker.

18
00:01:53,973 --> 00:01:58,454
I am offering you the opportunity
to walk out with the money, Mr. Bond.

19
00:01:58,692 --> 00:02:02,054
I'm giving you the opportunity
to walk out alive.

20
00:02:02,294 --> 00:02:05,735
Looking at our present situation,
strictly as a banker,

21
00:02:05,973 --> 00:02:08,414
I'd say that the numbers
are not on your side.

22
00:02:08,654 --> 00:02:11,615
Perhaps you failed
to take into account my...

23
00:02:11,855 --> 00:02:15,294
hidden assets.

24
00:02:23,335 --> 00:02:27,215
Get up! You seem to have had
a small reversal of fortune.

25
00:02:27,455 --> 00:02:29,535
- Give me the name.
- I can't tell you.

26
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,816
Let's count to three.

27
00:02:32,056 --> 00:02:33,697
You can do that, can't you?

28
00:02:33,937 --> 00:02:36,296
One.

29
00:02:36,536 --> 00:02:38,136
Two.

30
00:02:38,377 --> 00:02:42,736
All right, but you'll have to protect me...

31
00:04:23,024 --> 00:04:26,225
MI6 HEADQUARTERS
LONDON

32
00:04:36,065 --> 00:04:39,506
James! Have you brought me
a souvenir from your trip?

33
00:04:39,746 --> 00:04:42,585
Chocolates? An engagement ring?

34
00:04:42,825 --> 00:04:46,306
I thought you might enjoy one of these.

35
00:04:46,546 --> 00:04:49,347
How romantic.

36
00:04:49,586 --> 00:04:53,387
I know exactly where to put that.

37
00:04:56,148 --> 00:04:59,267
Oh, Moneypenny.
The story of our relationship.

38
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:02,468
Close, but no cigar.

39
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:08,188
<i>I hate to tear you away, 007.</i>
Would you mind coming in?

40
00:05:08,468 --> 00:05:11,347
Right away, M.

41
00:05:11,587 --> 00:05:14,548
Sir Robert King, James Bond.

42
00:05:14,789 --> 00:05:18,348
Ah, the man who retrieved my money.
I can't thank you enough.

43
00:05:18,588 --> 00:05:20,829
Careful, M. I might steal him from you.

44
00:05:21,069 --> 00:05:24,310
Construction's not exactly
my... speciality.

45
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:26,189
Quite the opposite, in fact.

46
00:05:26,429 --> 00:05:29,990
Best to the family.

47
00:05:33,709 --> 00:05:37,831
- Old friend?
- We read law at Oxford together.

48
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:41,030
I always knew he'd conquer the world.

49
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:44,471
- Care for a drink?
- Yes, thank you.

50
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:50,511
- He's a man of great integrity.
- Who buys stolen reports for £3m.

51
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:52,632
Thank you.

52
00:05:52,872 --> 00:05:56,872
- Any leads on the sniper?
- Not one. Professional job.

53
00:05:57,112 --> 00:06:00,233
She must be working for someone.
Is this the stolen report?

54
00:06:00,473 --> 00:06:03,752
Yes, classified, from the Russian
Atomic Energy Department.

55
00:06:03,992 --> 00:06:05,473
What would King want this for?

56
00:06:05,713 --> 00:06:08,992
He was led to believe
the document was a secret report,

57
00:06:09,232 --> 00:06:13,754
identifying the terrorists
who'd attacked his new oil pipeline.

58
00:06:13,994 --> 00:06:15,872
Interesting.

59
00:06:16,113 --> 00:06:22,073
But it doesn't explain why someone
would want me out of their office alive.

60
00:06:28,435 --> 00:06:33,915
- King! The money!
- Moneypenny, stop King.

61
00:06:39,435 --> 00:06:42,876
Move! Move! Move!

62
00:06:47,356 --> 00:06:49,997
Stop!

63
00:07:23,479 --> 00:07:24,679
Move!

64
00:07:24,919 --> 00:07:29,279
- Get out of the way!
- Medics coming through!

65
00:07:35,199 --> 00:07:40,041
Stop! Stop! It isn't finished!

66
00:11:12,777 --> 00:11:16,176
What was that?!

67
00:12:31,703 --> 00:12:33,942
- Let's go!
- What the hell do you think?

68
00:12:34,182 --> 00:12:37,383
Let's go!

69
00:13:02,464 --> 00:13:03,825
Listen to me!

70
00:13:04,065 --> 00:13:09,184
You can't get away. We can make a deal.
Who are you working for?

71
00:13:09,425 --> 00:13:12,146
Don't do it! Don't blow us up!

72
00:13:12,386 --> 00:13:15,465
I can protect you!
Do you understand? I can protect you.

73
00:13:15,705 --> 00:13:18,866
Not from him.

74
00:13:53,748 --> 00:13:58,828
# <i>I know how to hurt</i>

75
00:13:59,068 --> 00:14:04,030
# <i>I know how to heal</i>

76
00:14:04,268 --> 00:14:07,189
# <i>I know what to show</i>

77
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:13,590
# <i>And what to conceal</i>

78
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:20,150
# <i>I know when to talk</i>

79
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:25,670
# <i>And I know when to touch</i>

80
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:28,431
# <i>No-one ever died</i>

81
00:14:28,671 --> 00:14:33,711
# <i>From wanting too much</i>

82
00:14:33,951 --> 00:14:38,512
# <i>The world is not enough</i>

83
00:14:38,753 --> 00:14:41,672
# <i>But it is such a perfect place</i>

84
00:14:41,912 --> 00:14:44,913
# <i>To start, my love</i>

85
00:14:45,153 --> 00:14:48,992
# <i>And if you're strong enough</i>

86
00:14:49,232 --> 00:14:53,754
# <i>Together we can take the world apart</i>

87
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:58,033
# <i>My love</i>

88
00:14:58,073 --> 00:15:02,673
# <i>We know when to kiss</i>

89
00:15:02,913 --> 00:15:08,433
# <i>And we know when to kill</i>

90
00:15:08,673 --> 00:15:11,154
# <i>If we can't have it all</i>

91
00:15:11,394 --> 00:15:16,594
# <i>Then nobody will</i>

92
